<paragraph blockId="122.[784,1377,300,722]" box="[786,1185,453,486]" pageId="122" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[786,1185,453,486]" pageId="122" pageNumber="400">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="122.[784,1377,300,722]" pageId="122" pageNumber="400">
<taxonomicName authority="Bailey, 1902" authorityName="Bailey" authorityYear="1902" box="[787,1121,492,525]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Sigmodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="122" pageNumber="400" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="leucotis" subSpecies="leucotis">S. l. leucotis Bailey, 1902</taxonomicName>
— Y-shaped distri- butional pattern in Mexico from approxi- mately 27° N latitude in the Sierra Madre Occidental and 25° N in the Sierra Madre Oriental SE into the C part of the Trans- volcanic Beltas far S as the state of Mexico.
</paragraph>
